    <h1>Ten O’Clock News</h1>
    <p><em>The Ten O’Clock News</em>&nbsp;was a nightly news program produced and broadcast by WGBH. A local program aimed at the Boston audience,<em>The Ten O’Clock News</em>&nbsp;debuted on January 15, 1976. WGBH Media Library and Archives has preserved and described 523 tapes from<em>The Ten O’Clock News</em>, and its precursors,&nbsp;<em>The Reporters</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>Evening Compass</em>. Dating from 1974 to 1991, this collection focuses on news stories relating to Boston’s African American community. This project was funded by the&nbsp;<a target="_blank" href="http://www.imls.gov/index.shtm">Institute of Museum and Library Services.</a></p>

